Fiat Industrial, Popolare Milano, Snam May Move: Italian Equity Preview

-- B y   M a r c o   B e r t a c c h e   a n d   F r a n c e s c a   C i n e l l i
-- 
2011-04-21T06:51:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/fiat-industrial-popolare-milano-snam-italian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Italian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close.  Italy ’s benchmark  FTSE MIB Index (FTSEMIB)  increased 252.55, or 1.2
percent, to 21,502.45 yesterday.  Banca Popolare di Milano Scrl (PMI IM): Shares of the
Milan-based cooperative bank were cut to “underweight” from
“buy” at Banco Santander SA and to “underperform” from
“buy” at BofA Merrill Lynch Global Research. The stock dropped
8.6 percent to 2.31 euros.  Buzzi Unicem SpA (BZU)  : Italy’s second-biggest cement
maker was rated “neutral” in new coverage at JPMorgan Chase &
Co. The shares increased 4.1 percent to 9.85 euros.  Eni SpA (ENI)  : Italy’s biggest oil company was added to
the European “key calls” list at UBS AG. The shares gained 2.4
percent to 17.25 euros.  Fiat SpA (F)  : The carmaker said it reached an agreement
to exercise its option to purchase an additional 16 percent of
Chrysler. The company will pay $1.27 billion to exercise the
option. Fiat aims to complete a refinancing transaction for
Chrysler in the second quarter. The shares rose 4.6 percent to
6.58 euros.  Fiat Industrial SpA (FI IM): The truckmaker plans to report
first-quarter results. The shares advanced 1.6 percent to 10.15
euros.  Italcementi SpA (IT)  : JPMorgan Chase & Co. initiated
coverage of Italy’s biggest cement maker with an “underweight”
rating.  Separately, Goldman Sachs Group Inc. lifted its
recommendation to “neutral” from “sell.” The shares gained
2.5 percent to 7.11 euros.  Saipem SpA (SPM)  :  Europe ’s largest oilfield-services
contractor was upgraded to “buy” from “underweight” at
Gruppo Banca Leonardo. The shares added 2.1 percent to 37.63
euros.  Snam Rete Gas SpA (SRG)  : The owner of Italy’s natural-
gas grid plans to report first-quarter results. The shares rose
1.3 percent to 4.18 euros.  To contact the reporters on this story:
